issue.title: [V4] Error on useModal
issue.body:
I was looking for a way to update props/attrs of a dynamic modal from outside the modal. Luckily I found an existing issue stating that this will be part of next major release.
Thus, I migrated from v3 to v4 (RC) and followed the migration guide to switch from `$vfm.show()` to `useModal()` for dynamic modals.
But calling `useModal()` leads to an error in my browser's console (see below). Not sure if I did something wrong or if it is really a bug.

### Version

vue-final-modal: v4.0.0-rc.0
vue: 3.2.44
nuxt: Not installed

### OS

Linux

### Steps to reproduce
1. Install `vue-final-modal`
    ```vue
    import { createVfm } from 'vue-final-modal';
    const vfm = createVfm();
    app.use(vfm);
    ```
2. Call `useModal()` to create a modal
    ```vue
    import { useModal } from 'vue-final-modal';

    const {
        open,
        close,
        patchOptions,
    } = useModal({
        component: AddUser,
        attrs: {},
    });
    ```
3. Open page and try to open modal

### What is Expected?
Modal should open normally

### What is actually happening?
Modal does not open, error is thrown instead in the browser console (firefox in my case)
```
Uncaught TypeError: ae() is undefined
    Lt                        index.es.js:12
    showModal         modal.js:279
```

issue.title: [V4] Error on useModal
issue.body:
I was looking for a way to update props/attrs of a dynamic modal from outside the modal. Luckily I found an existing issue stating that this will be part of next major release.
Thus, I migrated from v3 to v4 (RC) and followed the migration guide to switch from `$vfm.show()` to `useModal()` for dynamic modals.
But calling `useModal()` leads to an error in my browser's console (see below). Not sure if I did something wrong or if it is really a bug.

### Version

vue-final-modal: v4.0.0-rc.0
vue: 3.2.44
nuxt: Not installed

### OS

Linux

### Steps to reproduce
1. Install `vue-final-modal`
    ```vue
    import { createVfm } from 'vue-final-modal';
    const vfm = createVfm();
    app.use(vfm);
    ```
2. Call `useModal()` to create a modal
    ```vue
    import { useModal } from 'vue-final-modal';

    const {
        open,
        close,
        patchOptions,
    } = useModal({
        component: AddUser,
        attrs: {},
    });
    ```
3. Open page and try to open modal

### What is Expected?
Modal should open normally

### What is actually happening?
Modal does not open, error is thrown instead in the browser console (firefox in my case)
```
Uncaught TypeError: ae() is undefined
    Lt                        index.es.js:12
    showModal         modal.js:279
```

I have to thank you for your great lib and support :heart:

issue.title: [V4] Error on useModal
issue.body:
I was looking for a way to update props/attrs of a dynamic modal from outside the modal. Luckily I found an existing issue stating that this will be part of next major release.
Thus, I migrated from v3 to v4 (RC) and followed the migration guide to switch from `$vfm.show()` to `useModal()` for dynamic modals.
But calling `useModal()` leads to an error in my browser's console (see below). Not sure if I did something wrong or if it is really a bug.

### Version

vue-final-modal: v4.0.0-rc.0
vue: 3.2.44
nuxt: Not installed

### OS

Linux

### Steps to reproduce
1. Install `vue-final-modal`
    ```vue
    import { createVfm } from 'vue-final-modal';
    const vfm = createVfm();
    app.use(vfm);
    ```
2. Call `useModal()` to create a modal
    ```vue
    import { useModal } from 'vue-final-modal';

    const {
        open,
        close,
        patchOptions,
    } = useModal({
        component: AddUser,
        attrs: {},
    });
    ```
3. Open page and try to open modal

### What is Expected?
Modal should open normally

### What is actually happening?
Modal does not open, error is thrown instead in the browser console (firefox in my case)
```
Uncaught TypeError: ae() is undefined
    Lt                        index.es.js:12
    showModal         modal.js:279
```

Wow, that was fast :astonished: :tada: 

I have to thank you for your great lib and support :heart:
